These great masters of Paris do read vast books, and turn over the
leaves with great diligence, which is a very good thing; but these
(spiritually enlightened men) read the true living book, wherein all
things liveï¼š they turn over the pages of the heavens and the earth,
and read therein the mighty and admirable wonders of God.
